---
<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service" description="HelixGitpx Terms of Service.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 prose prose-slate">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: 2026-04-21. Template pending legal review — see footer.</em></p>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">
      HelixGitpx is an open-source project (Apache-2.0 for code, CC-BY-SA-4.0
      for docs). These Terms apply to any hosted Service an operator runs from
      the project. The open-source software itself is governed solely by its
      license; no Terms attach to self-hosting.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Acceptance</h2>
    <p>By creating an account or using HelixGitpx ("Service"), you agree to these Terms. If you don't agree, do not use the Service.</p>

    <h2>2. Account</h2>
    <p>You're responsible for keeping your credentials secure and for all activity under your account. Notify us at <a href="mailto:security@helixgitpx.io">security@helixgitpx.io</a> immediately on suspected compromise.</p>

    <h2>3. Your content</h2>
    <p>You retain all rights to code and content you push through the Service. You grant HelixGitpx a limited licence to process, store, and mirror it solely to provide the Service and the upstream bindings you configure.</p>

    <h2>4. Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>No unlawful content, no malware distribution, no content that violates third-party rights, no use that disrupts or attempts to breach the Service. We reserve the right to suspend accounts for violations.</p>

    <h2>5. Availability</h2>
    <p>We target the SLO published on <a href="/trust">/trust</a>. For Team+ plans, see the service credit schedule in your order form.</p>

    <h2>6. Fees</h2>
    <p>Free plan is free. Paid plans bill monthly or annually per seat. Tax extra where applicable. No refunds for partial months except where required by law.</p>

    <h2>7. Termination</h2>
    <p>Either party may terminate with notice. On termination we export your data per our DPA and delete it within 30 days unless you request a different window.</p>

    <h2>8. Warranty & liability</h2>
    <p>The Service is provided "as is". To the extent permitted by law, HelixGitpx is not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages. Aggregate liability capped at fees paid in the 12 months preceding the claim.</p>

    <h2>9. Governing law</h2>
    <p>Set by the operator of the hosted Service per their order form. No default applies to the open-source software itself.</p>

    <h2>10. Contact</h2>
    <p>Operator-dependent. For the open-source project: file a GitHub issue.</p>

    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">
      ⚠️ <strong>Legal review pending.</strong> This page is a template, not
      a signed legal document. An operator running a hosted HelixGitpx
      Service must have this document reviewed by counsel before taking
      customers.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
